node.text:
Hey guys! Let me teach you how to paint xx

Things you’ll need:
- a black canvas / canvas panel (I’m using a monte mart 12x12” that I painted with black gesso)
- Liquin
- Phthalo blue blue oil paint 
- Titanium white oil paint
- A variety of Soft Tacklon Brushes some wide some detail.
- a pallet or pallet paper (you can use baking paper or tin foil)
- Some kitchen roll or rags from an old T-shirt
- thinners to clean your brushes after (Eg turps, oudourless thinners, white spirit etc)

node.text:
I’m doing another giveaway!! Woot woot! 🥳

This time last year I was preparing for Secret Store 2, which was the last glow in the dark collection I shared with you lovely people

So as me and my team prepare for our next big project (omg who else is excited?? 🙋‍♀️), I want to take this moment to celebrate the success that is the Secret Store 2’s anniversary. 

For those of you who don’t know, Secret Store 2 is extremely special as it is the record-holder of the fastest selling store I’ve ever had (16 freaking minutes)

My dudes everything was sold out in like 16 freaking minutes!! Wow! Just thinking about it now is giving me the goosebumps 

So anyway, what’s in this giveaway?

2 lucky space-loving creatures (you need to be a human from earth to qualify, okay?) will get a print from any of these designs

And yes, you get to pick IF YOU WIN. 

So how do you win?

To join the space fam appreciation giveaway, you only need to follow 3 simple steps 🥰
1. Follow @astronomy_eye & @cathrinmachin on Instagram
2. Sign up to the email list (link in bio), and share the last photo from this post to your IG story, you may encircle your fav design 💕
3. Comment here why you think that design stood out as the best

Their names are:

1 Andromeda
2 Stars over Sapa
3 Into the Beautiful Abyss
4 One Hologram Greater than Nothing
5 Horsehead Nebula
6 Guide me Home
7 Nuclei to Nebulae
8 Dream Big and Believe
9 Orion Nebula

I’ll be doing a bunch of Q&As here on Instagram to answer your questions so watch out for that x

node.text:
Hey guys! Let me teach you how to paint xx

Things you’ll need:
- a black canvas / canvas panel (I’m using a monte mart 12x12” that I painted with black gesso)
- Liquin
- Phthalo blue blue oil paint 
- Titanium white oil paint
- A variety of Soft Tacklon Brushes some wide some detail.
- a pallet or pallet paper (you can use baking paper or tin foil)
- Some kitchen roll or rags from an old T-shirt
- thinners to clean your brushes after (Eg turps, oudourless thinners, white spirit etc)

We’re days away from the official launch of my latest collection 🥳

Elements, as I call it, are five 12x12” original deep space artwork painted canvas panels, which features each of the 5 different elements: earth, wind, fire, water, air

Each piece is specially painted with pure pigments of Michael Harding oil paints

The whole collection will help fund a very special cause which you can read about in my recent post

I will be including a personal letter to everyone who will purchase any of the pieces from this collection. Though we’re days away the launch, I want to thank you in advance for your support to me and to Sarah, to whom I am dedicating this collection to

On a lighter note, I also want you to take a look at a very special member of the space fam in the last photo 😁✨

If you want in on any of these pieces (the big reveal is on Aug 16, 5PM PST) 🥰

node.text:
This is a very rare opportunity that I am thrilled to share with you ✨
I recently made 5 original artworks in 12 x 12 canvas panels calling the collection Elements as it makes me feel like the coming to life of the 5 elements (earth water fire wind & spirit) into deep space art 

The biggest reveal of all is that the Elements collection is to help my friend - Sarah who recently lost her best friend & cat, Fluffy. They were inseparable and spent everyday together. The incident happened a few days after Sarah's birthday, she received lilies as a gift. Fluffy ate them & was fatally poisoned.

Sarah & her family are now facing a massive vet bill & at the time of covid nonetheless. For anyone who’s ever had a bond with their pet, im certain you know the extent of this pain but more than that having to deal with the finances that come after. Doing all they can to save Fluffy’s life all to suffer a great loss all the same

Hoping we could do this small thing for Sarah & for anyone else who’s ever received unconditional love from pets who treat us as family - I want to raise awareness about how lilies are poisonous to animals as it doesn't seem to be common knowledge. Had any of us known, this wouldn’t have happened. The best we can do is let other people know

I almost never sell artwork like this cause there's a 2yr commission waiting list
Thank you so much for taking the time to read this far, I've written the instructions on how you can buy a special piece

Each piece will be 1080 USD- 7.5 USD per sq in, includes shipping & handling. If you’ve been watching me create deep space art for long now, you’ll also know that its super rare that I offer artworks at this size & price

🌌 Elements: Space Art Fundraiser for Sarah 🌌
1. On Aug 16 5PM PST I will announce the names of each artwork from Elements
2. To place an order send me a DM using the order form below
-Name of artwork
-Full name
-Email address
We’ll follow a first come, first served policy
3. Payment process info will be sent to you. We’ll be offering the artwork to the next person in line if you're unable to complete within 24h
Once payment has been verified by my team, we’ll send you confirmation of the sale

node.text:
Many of us don't really think about how life is short until we've lost someone close to our heart. I know that we've all gone through that grief and pain at many points in our lives but hey don't we all try to keep whatever was beautiful and lovely about that person we lost alive in ways we can?

This artwork is very very special to me and my friend, whose daughter has joined stars. To honor Niamh Carina's memory, we've named this artwork after her

I'm posting this now, with permission of course, to remind us that we must continue to remember the people we love who've passed. My friend shared that he and his wife really took their time to pick that name for her (and really, it's a beautiful name), so I wondered if I could ask you to take a moment to remember Carina, or any loved one of yours, if you see this on your timeline ✨

And let this be our reminder that space heals so we need to keep looking up 🌌 
Sending you the warmest hugs lovely 🥰

node.text:
Don’t expect to win, expect to work hard and you’ll always succeed.

Let me explain 
If you have expectations that 1 unit of work creates 50 units of value. 

Review your extreme worst case scenario. Eg 1 unit of work creates 5 units of value. 

If you instead expect to work 10 units of work to create 50 units of value.

If the worst case scenario happens you’ll be content.

If a not so good scenario happens you’ll be joyful

and if the high scenario happens you’ll be ecstatic 🥰
​
​Here's to breaking free from what holds us back... Happy 4th of July!🥳

So I got asked about the other artworks in the #SophiaXCathrin

Officially revealing the remastered version of the Aurora Borealis!!

This bad boy was originally part of my 1st ever collection called Beautifully Nerdy Deep Space Paintings, w/c also was my 1st Kickstarter project ✨

The lights from the Aurora Borealis also produce faint claps, crackles, & static sounds BUT the noise is so rare that hearing it is possible only during times of maximum aurora activity, on windless nights away from other noise 

Proud to make this a part of #SophiaXCathrin 😊

Btw hon, you can only get a piece of the #SophiaXCathrin if you’ve already signed up here catma.ch/SophiaXCathrin 

Your support means a lot to me and @astropartigirl, and really, every single #WomenInSTEAM
​ 
Sending tons of love your way 🥰

Getting tips from THE @Astropartigirl about how I can accurately depict the science behind my paintings has been the highlight of my week - especially for this Dark Matter Black Hole!!✨There are so many interactions within the black hole’s center and its outer regions that we have yet to understand, which are all going to be in Sophia’s dissertation!🌌

How cool is it that we get to support an actual scientific breakthrough? I can’t wait for Sophia to publish her dissertation on Dark Matter, its going to be amazing! 🥰

In the meantime, I hope you send some love for our upcoming store which opens on the 10th of June catma.ch/SophiaXCathrin
